      {
        "id": "ep-shipping-fee",
        "sectionId": "black-box-testing",
        "title": "Equivalence Partitioning - Shipping Fee",
        "description": "Group inputs and derive expected outcomes for shipping charges.",
        "createdAt": "2026-06-25T14:29:20.667Z",
        "updatedAt": "2026-06-25T15:34:07.643Z",
        "questions": [
          {
            "id": "ep-q1",
            "exerciseId": "ep-shipping-fee",
            "prompt": "The shipping fee is free for orders above $100. Which partition is valid?\n\n```ts\nconst freeShippingThreshold = 100;\n```",
            "explanation": "Equivalence partitioning divides inputs into valid and invalid classes.\n\n![Valid Partitions](https://placehold.co/640x220/png?text=Valid+Partitions)",
            "correctOptionId": "o-1782401648128-1",
            "orderIndex": 1,
            "options": [
              {
                "id": "o-1782401648128-0",
                "questionId": "ep-q1",
                "label": "A",
                "text": "Only orders worth `100`"
              },
              {
                "id": "o-1782401648128-1",
                "questionId": "ep-q1",
                "label": "B",
                "text": "Orders `<= 100` and orders `> 100`"
              },
              {
                "id": "o-1782401648128-2",
                "questionId": "ep-q1",
                "label": "C",
                "text": "Orders `1` to `10` only"
              },
              {
                "id": "o-1782401648128-3",
                "questionId": "ep-q1",
                "label": "D",
                "text": "Orders `100` and `200` only"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "ep-q2",
            "exerciseId": "ep-shipping-fee",
            "prompt": "Which formula describes the shipping fee rule if the base price is `p` and discount is `d`?\n\nUse $fee = p - d$ when the order is eligible for a discount.",
            "explanation": "The formula should match the business rule exactly.\n\n![Shipping Formula](https://placehold.co/640x220/png?text=Shipping+Formula)",
            "correctOptionId": "o-1782401648904-0",
            "orderIndex": 2,
            "options": [
              {
                "id": "o-1782401648904-0",
                "questionId": "ep-q2",
                "label": "A",
                "text": "$fee = p - d$"
              },
              {
                "id": "o-1782401648904-1",
                "questionId": "ep-q2",
                "label": "B",
                "text": "$fee = p + d$"
              },
              {
                "id": "o-1782401648904-2",
                "questionId": "ep-q2",
                "label": "C",
                "text": "$fee = d - p$"
              },
              {
                "id": "o-1782401648904-3",
                "questionId": "ep-q2",
                "label": "D",
                "text": "$fee = p \\times d$"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "ep-q3",
            "exerciseId": "ep-shipping-fee",
            "prompt": "A shipping calculator has these customer types. Which table best helps build equivalence classes?\n\n| Customer Type | Rule |\n| --- | --- |\n| Regular | Standard rate |\n| Premium | Discounted rate |\n\n![Customer Type Table](https://placehold.co/640x220/png?text=Customer+Type+Table)",
            "explanation": "Tables help compare groups of inputs and identify valid partitions quickly.\n\n![Equivalence Classes](https://placehold.co/640x240/png?text=Equivalence+Classes)",
